# Security

## Secrets and env

- Never commit secrets (`.env.local`, keys, tokens, service role).
- Only `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` may be exposed to the browser.
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY`, and `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` are **server-only**.
- Keep `.env.example` as placeholders only — never real values.

## Supabase access

- Prefer the anon/publishable key + user session on the client/SSR path.
- Use the service role only in trusted server code (Route Handlers / Server Actions) when RLS cannot cover the case — document why.
- Assume RLS is mandatory on user data tables; do not bypass it casually.

## App boundaries

- Firecrawl and DeepSeek must run only on the server (never from Client Components).
- Do not log secrets, access tokens, or full PII.
- Validate and sanitize all user input at the boundary (Server Actions / Route Handlers).
- Prefer least privilege: scope MCP / tooling to the Cestou project; avoid production data when experimenting.

## Checklist before finishing a task

- [ ] No secret in git diff
- [ ] No service role imported into client bundles
- [ ] Auth-sensitive routes protected (middleware / server checks)
- [ ] External API keys used only server-side
